line_1: Where with her birds of night, haggard and foul,
line_2: The bat ambiguous, and ill-omen'd owl,

line_1: There death deprive of all his terrours foul,
line_2: And sing soft requiems to the parting soul!

line_1: Like tapers glimmer'd on their orgies foul,
line_2: Re-echo'd loud by their tremendous howl!

line_1: So blending good with evil, fair with foul,
line_2: As thence to model one harmonious whole:

line_1: With gifts most meet for actions foul,
line_2: Her worms of conscience for the soul;

line_1: Those Eyes late blinded with disease so foul
line_2: With pointed Beams had shot thee to the Soul,

line_1: Methinks e'en now, within this dungeon foul,
line_2: I hear her vent her agony of soul.
Away the shocking image from my soul!

line_1: The bloated child of gorg'd intemperance foul;
line_2: Lowering, and foaming fierce with hideous howl
